external_knowledge:
- "promising prospects" refers to prospects with a rating greater than 4;
- "overall performance metrics" includes average projected points and the total number of prospects being evaluated;
- "latest news articles" are those with the most recent publication date.

sql:
SELECT conference_name
FROM conferences
WHERE established_year > 1990;

external_knowledge:
- "latest year" refers to the recruitment year 2023;
- "new students" refers to the total recruits for the year 2023;
- "overall potential judged to be on average" refers to the average prospect rating.

sql:
SELECT prospect_name, AVG(prospect_rating) AS average_rating
FROM prospects
GROUP BY prospect_name;

external_knowledge:
- "beacons of knowledge" metaphorically refers to esteemed conferences;
- "turned of the 20th century" refers to the year 1900;
- "first shine their light upon the academic firmament" represents the establishment of conferences;
- "date of first illumination" refers to the year a conference was established.

sql:
